: ...  And spread-spectrum transmissions used
: to be outlawed, execpt by a Special Test Authorization from the FCC,
: because they were hard to monitor.

Er? How on earth can you monitor spread spectrum transmissions?
Properly done they (transmissions) cannot even be detected, i.e. it
becomes impossible to even tell whether you are sending data or not.
(They may be able to tell if you transmitter is turned on...)

